The paper discusses a competition focused on reading Chinese text in natural images, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of large-scale datasets and evaluation protocols, which are common in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG) research. Finally, the competition involves end-to-end recognition, which is a popular topic in artificial intelligence (AI) research.
